    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"110596\">Rob Lewis</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/113488-general/topic/Lean's.20proof.20of.20FTA.20is.20.22obviously.20wrong.22/near/197057807\" title=\"#narrow/stream/113488-general/topic/Lean's.20proof.20of.20FTA.20is.20.22obviously.20wrong.22/near/197057807\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I'm happy to accept a PR to the CSS changing this. Actually, I had a vague memory of there being a PR already, but I don't see it.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Well, I wanted to do one in some topic, so I have a custom CSS userscript to remove those underlines personally and show them <em>only</em> on hover. It works pretty fine, I can bundle it into a PR.</p>",
        "id": 197057884,
